attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt families. The sample exhibits several classic malicious behaviors: it ensures single-instance execution via a lock file (/tmp/.bot_lock), employs anti-analysis techniques by checking for 'VMware' in the DMI product name, and daemonizes itself by forking and redirecting standard I/O to /dev/null. The core functionality includes a command parser (sub_408350) that listens for attack commands (prefixed with '!', e.g., !syn, !http, !udpplain) and implements multiple flooding routines including TCP SYN, UDP, and HTTP-based attacks. It also contains extensive process-scanning logic (sub_406040) that iterates through /proc to identify and potentially terminate competing processes or security tools.
